Walking through the familiar corridors, Lamin felt anger rise in him. This building was Ventrue, the very walls had been built with Ventrue blood. It pained and infuriated him to see Malkavian upstarts in the structure. Every one of them watched him carefully, and one even started to follow him. They probably expected him to rush over and rip their dirty throats out. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The idea does have a certain appeal...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Finding himself at the door of the meeting hall, he placed his hand on the handle. His meagre gift at psychometry told him that someone had used the door recently, but not who.<br>
Twisting the handle, Lamin pushed the door open, finding himself in the dark room, where there were ten of his Kindred sat around the large table in the centre. Several were looking at him. He spread his arms and grinned apologetically.<br>
&quot;Apologies for my lateness, my friends.&quot; he said to them, his french accent leaking into his speech. &quot;The time got away from me.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>So did the human,</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he thought, amused. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He was quite fast. Still, he's face down in an alley somewhere now, with about as much blood as a turnip.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Taking a seat which was as far away from Trekondar as possible, Lamin found himself opposite Ludria. She was staring at him with that familiar icy-eyed expression, which she seemed so good at. Lamin grinned at her, which had as much effect as throwing stones at a glacier.<br>
Looking around, Lamin saw somebody stand, and settled back in the chair to try to find out what this meeting was about. Under his coat, in its sheath on his belt, he felt the family dagger which he always carried with him, a comforting presence. He clutched the hilt lightly as another vampire began to speak.<br>
<br>
