<br>
IC:  Trekondar stood up, it appeared as though all who were going to attend had shown up.<br>
<br>
Clearing his throat, Trekondar began to speak in the same voice he always used for such occasions.<br>
<br>
&quot;It would appear to me as though we are lacking some members, I appreciate the reports I have gotten from everybody who has been kind enough to give one.  However, this is not merely a meeting to determine how each clan is doing, or even WHAT they are doing.  Rather it is a meeting which is of importance to all.  It would appear as though many things have been going on here inside the city with which I find myself rather unhappy about.  There also appear to be things going on with which I am unhappy about that are taking place OUTSIDE the city walls.&quot;  Trekondar stressed the word outside, causing the room to resonante with his voice.  He hoped it would strike home that the concerns of the clans was not only things happening inside the city, but outside as well.<br>
<br>
&quot;It appears as though we have had many Kindred turn up dead inside the city walls, or else just flat out disappear.  I am rather unhappy about this and will get to it at a later time.  However, since ages ago, Kindred have been locked into an eternal struggle with a race of subhumans, shapechangers... half man... half beast.  It appears that packs of Garou have been massing outside the city to the North and East where the city is bordered by forests.  Also, it appears the Slayers are on the upswing.  Both may cause problems for us in the future.  I believe that the dead bodies may be attributed to wererats.  I do not know that Craven or any of his clan have seen them but they have been lurking about in the city, and I know that they might frequent the sewers.  They may be the source of the missing bodies.  The Slayers are working very secretively, as I have as yet found any for sure, but I've seen their handiwork across the city from time to time.  And they may be the cause of the bodies that are found and are dead.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Also on a seperate note... there have been rumors floating about.  These rumors have said that the Ventrue are starting to form allegiances with some of the clans, and are planning to attempt a coup against the Malkavian Clan.  I say, if anybody is caught knowing anything of this, the they will be dealt with swiftly, and severely.  Treason is something that will not be tolerated, and Kain has assured me that he has a group of the Assamite Clan set aside specially for dealing with these matters.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that, Trekondar sat down and turned the floor back over to everyone else.<br>
